# {{ project_name }} — Web

Vite + React + TypeScript + Tailwind v4 + shadcn frontend.

---

## Quickstart

```bash
mise install            # installs Node 24 + pnpm via .mise.toml
pnpm install            # install deps from the shipped lockfile
pnpm dev                # Vite dev server at http://localhost:5173
```

Or from the project root (uses the polarity-aware `just dev` recipe):

```bash
just dev
```

---

## `just dev` polarity behaviour

The root `justfile` has a polarity-aware `dev` recipe:

| `has_web` | `has_backend` | `just dev` does |
|-----------|---------------|-----------------|
| true      | true          | `mprocs` starts Vite (:5173) + uvicorn (:8000) in a split-pane TUI |
| true      | false         | `pnpm --dir web dev` (Vite only — frontend-only mode) |
| false     | true          | `uv run uvicorn ...` (API only) |
| false     | false         | recipe absent — `just dev` will error |

Press Ctrl-C in the `mprocs` TUI to stop both processes.

