## Dark mode

The gallery header contains a `DarkModeToggle` component that sets
`document.documentElement.classList.toggle("dark")`. Tailwind v4 reads
the `dark` class on `<html>` to activate the dark-mode color tokens
(declared in `src/index.css` as `.dark { --color-background: ...; }`).

The `ThemeProvider` from `next-themes` wraps the app in `src/main.tsx`
so the initial system preference is applied before first paint.

---

## Replacing the gallery

`src/App.tsx` is a dev-only component gallery. To ship your real UI:

1. Delete the gallery sections inside `<main>`.
2. Add your own components.
3. Keep the `data-lost-pixel-id="..."` attributes on the sections you
   want to capture in Lost Pixel visual regression snapshots (plan 07-06).
4. If you no longer use Lost Pixel, remove the attributes entirely.

